TITLE: Creating and Resolving a Basic Promise in PHP
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to create a Promise object with wait and cancel functions, and how to resolve and wait for the promise to complete.
SOURCE: https://github.com/opencart/opencart/blob/master/upload/system/storage/vendor/guzzlehttp/promises/README.md#2025-04-19_snippet_13

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
use GuzzleHttp\Promise\Promise;

$promise = new Promise(
    function () use (&$promise) {
        $promise->resolve('waited');
    },
    function () {
        // do something that will cancel the promise computation (e.g., close
        // a socket, cancel a database query, etc...)
    }
);

assert('waited' === $promise->wait());
```

