TITLE: Non-unwrapping Promise Resolution with wait(false)
DESCRIPTION: Example showing how to force a promise to resolve without unwrapping its state by passing false to the wait() method, which prevents exceptions from being thrown.
SOURCE: https://github.com/opencart/opencart/blob/master/upload/system/storage/vendor/guzzlehttp/promises/README.md#2025-04-19_snippet_12

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
$promise = new Promise();
$promise->reject('foo');
// This will not throw an exception. It simply ensures the promise has
// been resolved.
$promise->wait(false);
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Implementing a Data Transformation Hook in Flot
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use the processDatapoints hook to transform data before plotting. This example multiplies all y-coordinates by 2, showing how to traverse and modify the normalized data points.
SOURCE: https://github.com/opencart/opencart/blob/master/upload/admin/view/javascript/jquery/flot/API.md#2025-04-19_snippet_54

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
function multiply(plot, series, datapoints) {
    var points = datapoints.points, ps = datapoints.pointsize;
    for (var i = 0; i < points.length; i += ps)
        points[i + 1] *= 2;
}
```

