TITLE: Promise Forwarding with Multiple Promises
DESCRIPTION: Example showing how to forward promises in a chain, where returning a promise in a 'then' callback causes subsequent promises to wait for the returned promise to be fulfilled.
SOURCE: https://github.com/opencart/opencart/blob/master/upload/system/storage/vendor/guzzlehttp/promises/README.md#2025-04-19_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
use GuzzleHttp\Promise\Promise;

$promise = new Promise();
$nextPromise = new Promise();

$promise
    ->then(function ($value) use ($nextPromise) {
        echo $value;
        return $nextPromise;
    })
    ->then(function ($value) {
        echo $value;
    });

// Triggers the first callback and outputs "A"
$promise->resolve('A');
// Triggers the second callback and outputs "B"
$nextPromise->resolve('B');
```

