TITLE: Creating Custom Stream Decorators with StreamDecoratorTrait in PHP
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to create a custom stream decorator using the StreamDecoratorTrait. This example implements a stream that executes a callback when EOF is reached.
SOURCE: https://github.com/opencart/opencart/blob/master/upload/system/storage/vendor/guzzlehttp/psr7/README.md#2025-04-19_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
use Psr\Http\Message\StreamInterface;
use GuzzleHttp\Psr7\StreamDecoratorTrait;

class EofCallbackStream implements StreamInterface
{
    use StreamDecoratorTrait;

    private $callback;

    private $stream;

    public function __construct(StreamInterface $stream, callable $cb)
    {
        $this->stream = $stream;
        $this->callback = $cb;
    }

    public function read($length)
    {
        $result = $this->stream->read($length);

        // Invoke the callback when EOF is hit.
        if ($this->eof()) {
            ($this->callback)();
        }

        return $result;
    }
}
```

